<article class="comment" id="comment5764851" data-author="users/48018" data-subject="comments/5764851" data-dislikes="0" data-id="5764851">
<p class="avatar"><a rel="nofollow" title="Norwegianguy" href="/users/Norwegianguy"><img class="framed lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA4MCA4MCI+PC9zdmc+" width="80" height="80" data-original="https://static.nintendolife.com/themes/nl.v10/images/avatar.jpg" alt="Norwegianguy" /></a></p>
<div class="detail"><ul class="info"><li class=" first"><a class="num" rel="nofollow" href="news/2020/08/random_nintendo_posts_new_image_of_mario_in_the_sunshine_internet_goes_wild_again#comment5764851">86</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow" class="username accent" title="Norwegianguy" href="/users/Norwegianguy">Norwegianguy</a></li><li class=" last"><time class="date age " datetime="2020-08-12T19:04:30+00:00"><span>Wed 12th Aug 2020</span></time></li></ul>
<section class="text">
<p>If these ports of 3D Mario games is all Nintendo has planned for the rest of the year, then that is quite dissappoiting. I would go as far as to say its one of the worst year Nintendo has had in recent times.</p><p>I know New Horizons sold incredible well and maybe Paper Mario sold decent, but in terms of having variety in games to cater to most of the Nintendo fans, is non existing. Two big first party games, a bunch indies, Xenoblade which, lets be honest, is a niche game, and ports of all the 3D Mario games for the holiday season? It's insane if Nintendo thinks this is acceptable.</p><p>A new DK game and Metroid wouldn't be too much to ask for? Pikmin 3? They had time and resourches to realease Pikmin 3 deluxe, but not a new game? Whats that about? A sequel to Mario x Rabbids has got to be in works. Why not show that game? Create some hype. Same goes for BOTW 2. We know they have been working on that game since early 2017. Couldn't they come up with a trailer at least? Showing us the final name of the game.</p><p>Im just flabbergasted at Nintendo right now..</p></section>
